## 6. Authentication & Session Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User (Browser)
    participant FE as React App
    participant BE as FastAPI
    participant DB as SQLite DB
    participant Mail as SMTP

    Note over U,Mail: ─── REGISTRATION ───
    U->>FE: Fill Signup Form
    FE->>BE: POST /auth/register {encrypted_pass}
    BE->>BE: decrypt_payload() → validate
    BE->>DB: Create User + Investor/Advisor record
    BE->>DB: Create OTP record (10 min TTL)
    BE-->>Mail: send OTP email (background)
    BE-->>FE: 201 {message}
    FE->>U: Navigate → /verify-otp
    U->>FE: Enter OTP
    FE->>BE: POST /auth/verify-otp
    BE->>DB: Mark OTP used, user.is_verified=True
    BE-->>FE: 200 OK

    Note over U,Mail: ─── LOGIN (2FA) ───
    U->>FE: Email + Password
    FE->>BE: POST /auth/login {encrypted_pass}
    BE->>DB: Verify credentials + is_verified
    BE->>DB: Store new OTP (login OTP)
    BE-->>FE: {status: otp_required, email}
    U->>FE: Click "Resend OTP"
    FE->>BE: POST /auth/resend-login-otp
    BE-->>Mail: send login OTP email
    U->>FE: Enter OTP
    FE->>BE: POST /auth/verify-login-otp
    BE->>DB: Mark OTP used
    BE-->>Mail: send login notification (background)
    BE-->>FE: {access_token, refresh_token, role}
    FE->>FE: Store tokens in localStorage
    FE->>U: Navigate → role-based dashboard

    Note over U,Mail: ─── TOKEN REFRESH ───
    FE->>BE: Any request → 401
    FE->>BE: POST /auth/refresh {refresh_token}
    BE->>DB: Check TokenBlacklist
    BE->>DB: Blacklist old token (rotation)
    BE-->>FE: {new_access_token, new_refresh_token}

    Note over U,Mail: ─── LOGOUT ───
    U->>FE: Logout
    FE->>BE: POST /auth/logout {refresh_token}
    BE->>DB: Blacklist refresh_token
    FE->>FE: Clear localStorage → /signin
```

---

## 7. Investment & Recommendation Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as Investor
    participant FE as ClientDashboard
    participant BE as FastAPI
    participant RISK as Risk Engine
    participant DB as SQLite
    participant Mail as SMTP

    Note over U,Mail: ── RISK PROFILING ──
    U->>FE: Open RiskProfileModal (Q1-Q4 + income + duration)
    FE->>BE: PUT /investor/profile {q1,q2,q3,q4,income,duration,dob}
    BE->>RISK: UserRiskScoreEngine.calculate_new/old_user_score()
    RISK-->>BE: {stated_risk, capacity_risk, revealed_risk, final_risk_score}
    BE->>DB: Update Investor record with risk scores
    BE-->>FE: InvestorResponse {risk_profile, final_risk_score}

    Note over U,Mail: ── GET RECOMMENDATIONS ──
    U->>FE: Enter amount + duration (+ optional risk override)
    FE->>BE: POST /recommendations/ {amount, duration, risk_override?}
    BE->>RISK: risk_level_to_score() + calculate_risk_capacity()
    BE->>DB: Query MutualFund + FundMetrics (active + complete metrics)
    BE->>BE: Filter by risk band (±0.30 of user score)
    BE->>BE: Score funds: W_FQS*FQS - W_RM*RiskMismatch + W_DF*DurationFit
    BE->>BE: Waterfall Allocation (25% cap per fund, min_investment check)
    BE-->>FE: RecommendationResponse {items[], total_allocated, explanation}

    Note over U,Mail: ── INVEST ──
    U->>FE: Click "Invest All"
    FE->>BE: POST /investor/invest-all {items[{scheme_code, amount}]}
    BE->>DB: Create PortfolioTransaction(s) → status=PENDING
    BE->>RISK: Recalculate risk profile post-investment
    BE-->>Mail: Notify advisor of pending order (background)
    BE-->>FE: {orders_placed, total_amount}

    Note over U,Mail: ── ADVISOR APPROVAL ──
    Mail-->>Advisor: Pending order email
    Advisor->>BE: POST /advisor/orders/{id}/approve
    BE->>DB: tx.status = "APPROVED"
    BE-->>Mail: Email investor (approved) + advisor (confirmation)
    Advisor->>BE: POST /advisor/orders/{id}/reject {reason}
    BE->>DB: tx.status = "REJECTED"
    BE-->>Mail: Email investor (rejected)
```

---

## 8. Risk Scoring Engine (Mathematical Detail)

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph Input["Inputs"]
        Q["Q1, Q2, Q3, Q4\n(Questionnaire 1-4 scale)"]
        Demo["Age, Annual Income\nInvestment Duration"]
        Portfolio["Portfolio Holdings\n(for 'Old' users)"]
    end

    subgraph Engine["UserRiskScoreEngine (core/)"]
        SR["Stated Risk Score\n= (avg(Q1-Q4) - 1) / 3\n→ normalized 0-1"]
        RC["Risk Capacity\n= 0.4*AgeScore + 0.3*IncomeScore + 0.3*DurationScore"]
        PRE["Past Risk Exposure\n= Σ(weight_i × FRS_i)"]
        VT["Volatility Tolerance\n= Portfolio_Vol / Market_Vol"]
        DT["Drawdown Tolerance\n= User_MDD / Market_MDD"]
        RR["Revealed Risk\n= 0.4*PRE + 0.4*VT + 0.2*DT"]
        ALPHA["Alpha Decay\n= exp(-0.5 × history_years)\nclamped [0.2, 0.5]"]
    end

    subgraph Output["Final Risk Score"]
        NEW["New User:\nFinal = 0.5*StatedRisk + 0.5*RiskCapacity"]
        OLD["Old User:\nFinal = α*StatedRisk + (1-α)*RevealedRisk"]
        LABEL["Risk Profile Label\n≤0.33 → Low Risk\n≤0.66 → Moderate\n>0.66 → High Risk"]
    end

    Q --> SR
    Demo --> RC
    Demo --> ALPHA
    Portfolio --> PRE
    Portfolio --> VT
    Portfolio --> DT
    PRE --> RR
    VT --> RR
    DT --> RR

    SR --> NEW
    RC --> NEW
    SR --> OLD
    RR --> OLD
    ALPHA --> OLD

    NEW --> LABEL
    OLD --> LABEL
```

---

## 9. Fund Recommendation Scoring Algorithm

```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph Weights
        W1["W_FQS = 0.50\n(Fund Quality Score)"]
        W2["W_RM = 0.30\n(Risk Mismatch penalty)"]
        W3["W_DF = 0.20\n(Duration Fit)"]
    end

    subgraph PerFund["Per Fund Calculation"]
        FQS["Fund Quality Score\n(pre-computed in DB)"]
        FRS["Fund Risk Score\n(pre-computed in DB)"]
        RM["Risk Mismatch\n= |UserRiskScore - FRS|"]
        DF["Duration Fit\n= max(0, 1 - |UserDuration - FundIdealDuration|\n/ FundIdealDuration)"]
        FS["Final Score\n= 0.5*FQS - 0.3*RM + 0.2*DF"]
    end

    subgraph Allocation["Waterfall Allocation"]
        SORT["Sort by Final Score DESC"]
        BASKET["Size Basket\n≤20L → 4 funds\n≤1Cr → 5 funds\n≤5Cr → 6 funds\n>5Cr → max(min_funds×2, 8)"]
        CAP["Concentration Cap\n25% per fund\nAbs cap ₹10Cr"]
        ALLOC["Iterative Waterfall:\nDistribute proportionally\nRe-weight on cap-out"]
    end

    FQS --> FS
    RM --> FS
    DF --> FS
    W1 --> FS
    W2 --> FS
    W3 --> FS
    FS --> SORT --> BASKET --> CAP --> ALLOC
```

